quote.summary: Qingdao Port International Co Ltd is a China-based company mainly engaged in the provision of port-related services. The Company conducts businesses through five segments. The Container Handling and Ancillary Services segment is engaged in the loading and unloading, storage and port management of containers. The Metal Ore, Coal and Other Cargo Handling and Ancillary Services segment is engaged in the loading and unloading, storage and port management of metal ores, coal, grain, general cargo and other cargoes. The Liquid Bulk Handling and Ancillary Services segment is engaged in the loading and unloading, storage, transportation and port management of crude oil and other liquid bulk cargoes. The Logistics and Port Value-added Services segment is engaged in the terminal, logistics transportation, freight forwarding, barge, tallying and other businesses. The Port Ancillary Services segment is engaged in the power supply and oil supply of the port area.
